<h2>
    Introduction: Why Bend Is a Bass Angler’s Paradise
</h2>
<p>
    Bend may be best known for trout, but <strong>bass fishing near Bend, Oregon</strong> is on the rise. Within 90 minutes, anglers can access warmwater havens like <strong>Crane Prairie Reservoir</strong>, <strong>Prineville Reservoir</strong>, and <strong>Haystack Reservoir</strong>—teeming with both largemouth and smallmouth bass. From easy bank spots to scenic boat waters, Bend offers diverse, exciting bass opportunities for all anglers.&nbsp;
</p>
<h2>
    Types of Bass Around Bend
</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Largemouth Bass</strong>: Prefer weedy, shallow areas and are abundant in Crane Prairie Reservoir.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Smallmouth Bass</strong>: Found in rockier, clearer reservoirs like Prineville and Haystack.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Both species offer aggressive strikes and exciting fights, especially in spring and early summer.
</p>
